examples.en: It's costing us a fortune in phone bills.
His frequent absences ended up costing him his job.
Bad management could be costing this club a chance at the title.
Fraud is thought to be costing software companies millions of dollars a year.
The project will end up costing the government an estimated 3.5 billion dollars.
This new digital camera is a carbon of a well-known model costing almost twice as much.
